### Email Testing Workflow
### Prerequisites: Make sure the application is running (docker-compose up -d)

### 1. Create a test user
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/signup
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testuser2@example.com",
  "password": "testpass123",
  "firstName": "Test",
  "lastName": "User"
}

### 2. Sign in to get JWT token
POST http://localhost:3000/auth/signin
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "email": "testuser2@example.com",
  "password": "testpass123"
}

# Copy the "access_token" from the response above and use it in the Authorization headers below

### 3. Test receipt email
# Replace YOUR_JWT_TOKEN with the actual token from step 2
POST http://localhost:3000/billings/test/receipt
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

{
  "email": "akinbobolafaniyi@gmail.com",
  "name": "Test Customer",
  "invoiceNumber": "TEST-001",
  "amount": 2999,
  "currency": "usd",
  "planName": "Premium Monthly Plan"
}

### 4. Test renewal reminder email
# Replace YOUR_JWT_TOKEN with the actual token from step 2
POST http://localhost:3000/billings/test/renewal-reminder
Content-Type: application/json
Authorization: Bearer YOUR_JWT_TOKEN

{
  "email": "akinbobolafaniyi@gmail.com",
  "name": "Test Customer",
  "planName": "Premium Monthly Plan",
  "amount": 2999,
  "currency": "usd",
  "subscriptionId": "sub_test_123"
}